    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In this article I’ll show you how to create and train a neural network using <a href="https://synaptic.juancazala.com/#/" target="_self">Synaptic.js</a>, which allows you to do deep learning in Node.js and the browser.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We’ll be creating the simplest neural network possible: one that manages to solve the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exclusive_or" target="_self">XOR equation.</a></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
